(
<figureCitation id="FDD1E3AFFFFAFFC5FF79FEF5FF0BFEEF" box="[159,246,295,321]" captionStart="FIGURE 11" captionStartId="64.[151,250,1965,1989]" captionTargetBox="[195,1391,191,1929]" captionTargetId="figure-32@64.[189,1399,181,1941]" captionTargetPageId="64" captionText="FIGURE 11. Eudocima kuehni and Eudocima cocalus group adults (dorsal aspect)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6605524" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6605524/files/figure.png" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">Figs 11</figureCitation>
: F–H, J, 20: D, 25: L, 31: L, 95: A–B)
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="6555FF2AFFFAFFC5FF71FE99FDEAFE03" blockId="18.[151,1436,258,429]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">
The diagnosis is provided under 
<taxonomicName id="A2EA84A9FFFAFFC5FDEAFE99FD7EFECB" baseAuthorityName="Cramer" baseAuthorityYear="1777" box="[524,643,331,357]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Eudocima" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cocalus">
<emphasis id="579E2338FFFAFFC5FDEAFE99FD7EFECB" box="[524,643,331,357]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">E. cocalus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
above. It is essentially a continental species (or phenotype) allopatric with nominate 
<emphasis id="579E2338FFFAFFC5FEA7FEBDFE40FE27" box="[321,445,367,393]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">
<taxonomicName id="A2EA84A9FFFAFFC5FEA7FEBDFE44FE27" baseAuthorityName="Cramer" baseAuthorityYear="1777" box="[321,441,367,393]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Eudocima" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cocalus">E. cocalus</taxonomicName>
,
</emphasis>
occurring from 
<collectingCountry id="1DFDBFBAFFFAFFC5FD91FEBDFD4CFE27" box="[631,689,367,393]" name="India" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">India</collectingCountry>
to southern 
<collectingCountry id="1DFDBFBAFFFAFFC5FCD8FEBDFC7CFE27" box="[830,897,367,393]" name="China" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">China</collectingCountry>
and all of Indochina south to the Andaman and Nicobar Islands (
<bibRefCitation id="017B82DBFFFAFFC5FEB0FE41FDF6FE03" author="Zilli, A. &amp; Brou, V. A. &amp; Klem, C. &amp; Zaspel, J." box="[342,523,403,429]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" pagination="152 - 166" refId="ref41849" refString="Zilli, A., Brou, V. A., Klem, C. &amp; Zaspel, J. (2017) The Eudocima Billberg, 1820 of the Australian Region (Lepidoptera: Erebidae). In: Telnov, D. (Ed.), Biodiversity, Biogeography and Nature Conservation in Wallacea and New Guinea. Vol. 3. The Entomological Society of Latvia, Riga, pp. 631 - 655, pls. 152 - 166." type="book chapter" year="2017">
Zilli 
<emphasis id="579E2338FFFAFFC5FE69FE41FE3DFE03" box="[399,448,403,429]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">et al</emphasis>
. 2017
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
